== Potato Wedges ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel) then pop onto a
lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.
Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until
golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

== Herby Carrots ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @parsley{5%g}(finely chopped, stalks and all).

Trim the @carrots{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into
roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop onto a large (lined) baking tray.

Drizzle with oil, season with a pinch of salt and pepper then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer and roast until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

== Beef ==

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of oil. Season the
@Irish Beef Rump{250%g} with salt and pepper.

When the pan is hot, fry the beef until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side
for medium-rare.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Cook ~{1-2%minutes} more each side for medium.

Once ready, remove from pan, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest. Meat is
safe to eat when outside is browned.

> TIP: Cook an extra 1-2 mins each side if you want it well done.

Once the beef is cooked, transfer to a #plate{}.

Spread the @harissa paste{1%sachet} evenly over the top with a #spoon{}.

Cover with foil and leave to the side to rest.

To a #bowl{}, add the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} along with 1 tbsp oil (double
for 4p) and half the parsley.

Season to taste with salt and pepper, mix well then set aside.

Return the pan to a medium-high heat with another drizzle of oil and
@butter{1%tsp} (double for 4p).

Add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Remove from the heat and add the cooked carrots to the pan along with the
parsley dressing. Toss to coat.

Thinly slice and divide the beef rump between plates with the potato wedges
and carrots alongside.

Drizzle over any juices from the resting meat.

Garnish with a sprinkle of the remaining parsley.